I hate to gripe, but this 45-second lag while AGX deletes old .cfg files is just killing me. I know I can turn it off, but then I assume I have to go periodically purge them manually. I guarantee I'm going to forget to do that, and then who knows what will happen. Is there any hope of AGX just integrating directly into the save file?

45 second lag? How many save files (files ending in .sfs) do you have?

The delay is proportional to the count of those .sfs files as it has to access each one to see which AGExt#####.cfg to keep for that file and KSP has a very slow disk access method I am limited. If you can delete some of those .sfs files, that would speed up the transition.

Just to confirm, you are only seeing this lag on the first Main Menu -> Space Center switch correct? If it is happening more often then that something is up and I will need bug report to fix whatever is going on.

As for integrating with the data file, that is not currently planned. I actually used to use the data file directly, but a few version ago there was a bug where partModules (the in-data file storage method) would reset to default on vessel load. This resulted in all actions being lost because the default state is no actions assigned. I had to break the actions out into their own file like this just to get them to save at all at the time. While this bug has since been fixed everything works as is so my focus has been adding features.

Having said that, I do consider doing it every so often, the biggest hurdle at this point is I save data in my files that has no equivalent in the default save file. This means that it is not a simple change of saying "save over here instead", I'd actually have to rewrite about 50% of my save load code and that's a huge undertaking.

D.

45 second lag? How many save files (files ending in .sfs) do you have?

About 80

If you can delete some of those .sfs files, that would speed up the transition.

How do I know which ones are safe to delete?

Just to confirm, you are only seeing this lag on the first Main Menu -> Space Center switch correct?

Correct.

Hi, I noticed that AGX 1.31f is causing a very disturbing increasing lag during long travels (ex. to Jool) on my Ubuntu (Linux64) install. If I change to Space Center and back the lag disappears.

I tested this on a fresh copy with only Mechjeb and KW Rocketry installed. I hope this helps.

@thegreatgonz: The "persistent.sfs" file is the current save that is updated anytime you scene change. The "quicksave.sfs" is the save file used by the F5-F9 quicksave system. Any other .sfs files in that folder were created by you manually through the Save function in the main menu, or you have an auto-backup/auto-save mod of some sort installed.

Apart from that, is sounds like everything is technically functioning as intended. Due to how KSP modding works, I am stuck using KSP to open those files and that is unfortunately a very slow process. I didn't realize it was 2 files per second slow though.

While things are kind of in limbo until KSP 1.0 hits (I don't want to be in the middle of making changes when that happens), I'll see if there is something I can do to mitigate this once things settle down afterwards.

@rainerd66: That is certainly something I need to look into, I will need more details though. Is is a gradually slow-down? Is there anything in the log at all? (Note it might be something in the log upon entering the flight scene, not just at the time the slow-down is happening.) Do you know if it seemed to start with version 1.31f and a previous version was fine? Are you switching ships or is it a single ship on a timewarp voyage?

D.

Can this apply actions to an entire group of a single part type at once? Like say lots of individual drills?

I'm trying to make a kerbinside ground refinery with a massive amount of drills and I don't want to have to set action group for every. single. one. Mirror symmetry helps a bit, but given how it's going to have hundreds of drills......

I think I'll go and check this out to see what it does.

Edited April 15, 2015 by smjjames

@smjjames: There is an option to select parts by type. Make sure no parts are currently selected by clicking the "Clear List" button, then click the "Show List of Parts" button that appears in the selected parts window. The groups window will change to show a list of all part types on the vessel and when you select a type, all parts of that type will be selected and you can assign the actions.

You would have to repeat this for each type of drill as only one specific type of part can be selected at once, but it saves you from having to click on each drill, or mirror selection of drills, individuality.

Hope that helps,

D.
